{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"51501","heading":"Establishment of Office of Spaceports","label":"51501 Establishment of Office of Spaceports","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/stV/ch515","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this section, referred to in subsec. (a), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 115–254Oct. 5, 2018"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment of Office","label":"a .—Establishment of Office","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 90 days after the date of enactment of this section, the Secretary of Transportation shall identify, within the Office of Commercial Space Transportation, a centralized policy office to be known as the Office of Spaceports.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Functions","label":"b .—Functions","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"support licensing activities for operation of launch and reentry sites;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop policies that promote infrastructure improvements at spaceports;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide technical assistance and guidance to spaceports;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"promote United States spaceports within the Department; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"strengthen the Nation’s competitiveness in commercial space transportation infrastructure and increase resilience for the Federal Government and commercial customers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Recognition","label":"c .—Recognition","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"launches to or reentries from orbit; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"are involved in suborbital launch activities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Director","label":"d .—Director","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The head of the Office of the Associate Administrator for Commercial Space Transportation shall designate a Director of the Office of Spaceports.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Definition","label":"e .—Definition","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t51/s51501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft51%2Fs51501%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section the term “spaceport” means a launch or reentry site that is operated by an entity licensed by the Secretary of Transportation.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
